      "enGB": "Arcane Metamastery — Solid Shadows",
      "enGB": "Flaming Burst",
      "enGB": "A flaming burst weapon explodes with flame upon striking a successful critical hit. The fire does not harm the wielder. A flaming burst weapon deals an extra 1d10 points of fire damage on a successful critical hit. Add an extra 1d10 points of fire damage for every critical multiplier beyond 2.",
      "enGB": "Arcane Weapon — Flaming Burst",
      "enGB": "Icy Burst",
      "enGB": "An icy burst weapon explodes with ice upon striking a successful critical hit. The cold does not harm the wielder. An icy burst weapon deals an extra 1d10 points of cold damage on a successful critical hit. Add an extra 1d10 points of cold damage for every critical multiplier beyond 2.",
      "enGB": "Arcane Weapon — Icy Burst",
      "enGB": "Shocking Burst",
      "enGB": "A shocking burst weapon explodes with electricity upon striking a successful critical hit. The electricity does not harm the wielder. A shocking burst weapon deals an extra 1d10 points of electricity damage on a successful critical hit. Add an extra 1d10 points of electricity damage for every critical multiplier beyond 2.",
      "enGB": "Arcane Weapon — Shocking Burst",
      "enGB": "An arcanist with this exploit can acquire a familiar as the arcane bond wizard class feature. A familiar is a magical pet that enhances the wizard's skills and senses",
      "enGB": "Familiar",
      "enGB": "The arcanist can select one item creation feat as a bonus feat. She must meet the prerequisites of this feat.",
      "enGB": "Item Crafting",
      "enGB": "The arcanist can select one metamagic feat as a bonus feat. She must meet the prerequisites of this feat.",
      "enGB": "Metamagic Knowledge",
      "enGB": "Greater Metamagic Knowledge",
      "enGB": "The arcanist can prepare a spell in place of an existing spell by expending 1 point from her arcane reservoir. Using this ability is a full-round action that provokes an attack of opportunity. The spell prepared must be of the same level as the spell being replaced.",
      "enGB": "Quick Study",
      "enGB": "While wearing armor, the fighter gains a bonus on Intimidate checks based upon the type of armor he is wearing: +1 for light armor, +2 for medium armor, or +3 for heavy armor. This bonus increases by 1 at 7th level and every 4 fighter levels thereafter, to a maximum of +4 at 19th level.",
      "enGB": "Armored Confidence",
      "enGB": "Armored Confidence Effect",
      "enGB": "When wearing heavy armor, the fighter gains DR 1/—. At 7th level, the fighter gains DR 1/— when wearing medium armor, and DR 2/— when wearing heavy armor. At 11th level, the fighter gains DR 1/— when wearing light armor, DR 2/— when wearing medium armor, and DR 3/— when wearing heavy armor. If the fighter is 19th level and has the armor mastery class feature, these DR values increase by 5. The DR from this ability stacks with that provided by adamantine armor, but not with other forms of damage reduction.",
      "enGB": "When wearing heavy armor, the fighter gains DR 1/—. At 7th level, the fighter gains DR 1/— when wearing medium armor, and DR 2/— when wearing heavy armor. At 11th level, the fighter gains DR 1/— when wearing light armor, DR 2/— when wearing medium armor, and DR 3/— when wearing heavy armor. The DR from this ability stacks with other DR/-",
      "enGB": "Armored Juggernaut",
      "enGB": "Armored Juggernaut Effect",
      "enGB": "You treat the armor bonus from your armor as 50% higher than normal, to a maximum increase of half your mythic rank plus one.",
      "enGB": "Armored Might",
      "enGB": "Mythic Heavy Armor — Assault",
      "enGB": "Mythic Heavy Armor — Endurance",
      "enGB": "Mythic Heavy Armor — Avoidance",
      "enGB": "Mythic Light Armor — Avoidance",
      "enGB": "Mythic Light Armor — Endurance",
      "enGB": "Mythic Light Armor — Assault",
      "enGB": "Mythic Medium Armor — Assault",
      "enGB": "Mythic Medium Armor — Avoidance",
      "enGB": "Mythic Medium Armor — Endurance",
      "enGB": "You don’t take an armor check penalty or incur an arcane spell failure chance when wearing heavy armor or using any shield. In addition, the maximum Dexterity bonus of heavy armor doesn’t apply to you.",
      "enGB": "Armor Master (Heavy Armor)",
      "enGB": "While wearing armor or wielding a shield, you reduce the armor check penalty by 1 per mythic rank and increase the maximum Dexterity bonus allowed by 1 per mythic rank. Additionally you reduce your arcane spell failure chance from armor and sheilds by 5% per mythic rank.",
      "enGB": "Armor Master",
      "enGB": "You don’t take an armor check penalty or incur an arcane spell failure chance when wearing light armor or using any shield. In addition, the maximum Dexterity bonus of light armor doesn’t apply to you.",
      "enGB": "Armor Master (Light Armor)",
      "enGB": "You don’t take an armor check penalty or incur an arcane spell failure chance when wearing medium armor or using any shield. In addition, the maximum Dexterity bonus of medium armor doesn’t apply to you.",
      "enGB": "Armor Master (Medium Armor)",
      "enGB": "You don’t take an armor check penalty or incur an arcane spell failure chance when wearing the selected armor types or using any shield. In addition, the maximum Dexterity bonus of the selected armor type doesn’t apply to you.",
      "enGB": "Armor Master (Tabletop)",
      "enGB": "Armor mastery feats are a new type of feat that require armor training as a prerequisite. They count as combat feats for all purposes, including which classes can select them as bonus feats. You gain the benefits of an armor mastery feat only while wearing armor with which you are proficient and only while wearing a type of armor that matches the feat’s armor proficiency feat prerequisite, if any. Armor mastery feats without armor proficiency prerequisites can be used while wearing any suit of armor. Characters who lack the armor training class feature can access armor mastery feats by taking a relevent Armor Focus feat.",
      "enGB": "Armor Mastery",
      "enGB": "Heavy Armor Specialization",
      "enGB": "The AC bonus granted by any heavy armor you equip increases by 1 for every 4 fighter levels you possess up to a maximum of 5.",
      "enGB": "Light Armor Specialization",
      "enGB": "The AC bonus granted by any light armor you equip increases by 1 for every 4 fighter levels you possess up to a maximum of 3.",
      "enGB": "Medium Armor Specialization",
      "enGB": "The AC bonus granted by any medium armor you equip increases by 1 for every 4 fighter levels you possess up to a maximum of 4.",
      "enGB": "The fighter selects one specific type of armor with which he is proficient, such as light or heavy. While wearing the selected type of armor, the fighter adds one-quarter of his fighter level to the armor’s armor bonus, up to a maximum bonus of +3 for light armor, +4 for medium armor, or +5 for heavy armor. This increase to the armor bonus doesn’t increase the benefit that the fighter gains from feats, class abilities, or other effects that are determined by his armor’s base armor bonus, including other advanced armor training options. A fighter can choose this option multiple times. Each time he chooses it, he applies its benefit to a different type of armor.",
      "enGB": "Armor Specialization",
      "enGB": "Armor Training",
      "enGB": "Armor Training Speed",
      "enGB": "Azata shares a bond with her dragon. 50% damage is redirected to Aivu. In addition, Aivu gets additional DR N/Lawful where N is equal to Azata's mythic rank.",
      "enGB": "Axiomatic",
      "enGB": "Acolyte adds <b><color=#703565><link=\"Encyclopedia:Persuasion\">Persuasion</link></color></b> and <b><color=#703565><link=\"Encyclopedia:Lore_Religion\">Lore (religion)</link></color></b> to the list of her class <b><color=#703565><link=\"Encyclopedia:Skills\">skills</link></color></b>. She can also use her <b><color=#703565><link=\"Encyclopedia:Wisdom\">Wisdom</link></color></b> instead of <b><color=#703565><link=\"Encyclopedia:Charisma\">Charisma</link></color></b> while attempting Persuasion <b><color=#703565><link=\"Encyclopedia:Check\">checks</link></color></b>.\nIf the character already has the class skill, <b><color=#703565><link=\"Encyclopedia:Weapon_Proficiency\">weapon proficiency</link></color></b> or armor proficiency granted by the selected background from her class during character creation, then the corresponding <b><color=#703565><link=\"Encyclopedia:Bonus\">bonuses</link></color></b> from background change to a +1 trait bonus in case of skills, a +1 trait bonus in case of weapon proficiency and a –1 <b><color=#703565><link=\"Encyclopedia:Armor_Check_Penalty\">Armor Check Penalty</link></color></b> reduction in case of armor proficiency.",
      "enGB": "Acrobat adds <b><color=#703565><link=\"Encyclopedia:Trickery\">Trickery</link></color></b> and <b><color=#703565><link=\"Encyclopedia:Mobility\">Mobility</link></color></b> to the list of her class <b><color=#703565><link=\"Encyclopedia:Skills\">skills</link></color></b>. She also becomes proficient with throwing axes.\nIf the character already has the class skill, <b><color=#703565><link=\"Encyclopedia:Weapon_Proficiency\">weapon proficiency</link></color></b> or armor proficiency granted by the selected background from her class during character creation, then the corresponding <b><color=#703565><link=\"Encyclopedia:Bonus\">bonuses</link></color></b> from background change to a +1 trait bonus in case of skills, a +1 trait bonus in case of weapon proficiency and a –1 <b><color=#703565><link=\"Encyclopedia:Armor_Check_Penalty\">Armor Check Penalty</link></color></b> reduction in case of armor proficiency.",
