      "enGB": "Your Black Blade takes the form of a Dwarven Waraxe.",
      "enGB": "Dwarven Waraxe",
      "enGB": "The Black Blade's ego increases by 2.",
      "enGB": "Black Blade Ego Increase",
      "enGB": "The Black Blade's ego increases by 3.",
      "enGB": "The Black Blade's ego increases by 4.",
      "enGB": "At 5th level, as a free action, a wielder can spend a point of his black blade’s arcane pool to have it deal one of the following types of damage instead of weapon damage: cold, electricity, or fire. He can spend 2 points from the black blade’s arcane pool to deal sonic or force damage instead of weapon damage. This effect lasts until the start of the wielder’s next turn.",
      "enGB": "At 5th level, as a free action, the wielder can spend a point of his black blade’s arcane pool to have it deal one of the following types of damage instead of weapon damage: cold, electricity, or fire. He can spend 2 points from the black blade’s arcane pool to deal sonic or force damage instead of weapon damage. This effect lasts until the start of the wielder’s next turn.",
      "enGB": "The Black Blade's damage is converted into cold damage.",
      "enGB": "Energy Attunement",
      "enGB": "1 round",
      "enGB": "Energy Attunement — Cold",
      "enGB": "The Black Blade's damage is converted into electricity damage.",
      "enGB": "Energy Attunement — Electricity",
      "enGB": "The Black Blade's damage is converted into fire damage.",
      "enGB": "Energy Attunement — Fire",
      "enGB": "The Black Blade's damage is converted into force damage.",
      "enGB": "Energy Attunement — Force",
      "enGB": "The Black Blade's damage is converted into sonic damage.",
      "enGB": "Energy Attunement — Sonic",
      "enGB": "Your Black Blade takes the form of a Falcata.",
      "enGB": "Falcata",
      "enGB": "Your Black Blade takes the form of a Handaxe.",
      "enGB": "Handaxe",
      "enGB": "Your Black Blade takes the form of a Kama.",
      "enGB": "Kama",
      "enGB": "Your Black Blade takes the form of a Kukri.",
      "enGB": "Kukri",
      "enGB": "At 19th level, each time the wielder kills a living creature with the black blade, he can pick one of the following effects: \nBlade - The Black Blade restores 2 points to its arcane pool.\nShared - The Black Blade restores 1 point to its arcane pool and the magus restores 1 point to his arcane pool\nWielder - The Wielder gains a number of temporary hit points equal to the black blade’s ego (these temporary hit points last until spent or 1 minute, whichever is shorter).",
      "enGB": "Life Drinker",
      "enGB": "Life Drinker — Blade",
      "enGB": "Each time the wielder kills a living creature with the black blade, the black blade restores 2 points of its arcane pool.",
      "enGB": "Life Drinker — Shared (Arcanist)",
      "enGB": "Each time the wielder kills a living creature with the black blade, the black blade restores 1 point to its arcane pool and the wielder restores 1 point to his arcane reservoir.",
      "enGB": "Life Drinker — Shared (Magus)",
      "enGB": "Each time the wielder kills a living creature with the black blade, the black blade restores 1 point to its arcane pool and the wielder restores 1 point to his arcane pool.",
      "enGB": "Life Drinker Temp HP",
      "enGB": "Life Drinker — Wielder",
      "enGB": "Each time the wielder kills a living creature with the black blade, the wielder gains a number of temporary hit points equal to the black blade’s ego (these temporary hit points last until spent or 1 minute, whichever is shorter).",
      "enGB": "Your Black Blade takes the form of a Longsword.",
      "enGB": "Longsword",
      "enGB": "The Black Blade's mental stats increase by 1.",
      "enGB": "Black Blade Stat Increase",
      "enGB": "At level 3 the you will gain a black blade that will grow stronger along side you.",
      "enGB": "Your Black Blade takes the form of a Rapier.",
      "enGB": "Rapier",
      "enGB": "Your Black Blade takes the form of a Sawtooth Sabre.",
      "enGB": "Sawtooth Sabre",
      "enGB": "Your Black Blade takes the form of a Scimitar.",
      "enGB": "Scimitar",
      "enGB": "At 3rd level, the bladebound magus’ gains a powerful sentient weapon called a black blade, whose weapon type is chosen by the magus. A magus with this class feature cannot take the familiar magus arcana, and cannot have a familiar of any kind, even from another class.",
      "enGB": "Black Blade Selection",
      "enGB": "Your Black Blade takes the form of a Shortsword.",
      "enGB": "Shortsword",
      "enGB": "Your Black Blade takes the form of a Sickle.",
      "enGB": "Sickle",
      "enGB": "A wielder of a black black of 17th level or higher can expend an arcane point from his weapon’s arcane pool as a free action; he then gains SR equal to his black blade’s ego until the start of his next turn.",
      "enGB": "Spell Defense",
      "enGB": "1 minute",
      "enGB": "As a free action, the magus can spend a point from the black blade’s arcane pool to grant the black blade a +1 bonus on damage rolls for 1 minute. For every four levels beyond 1st, this ability gives the black blade another +1 on damage rolls.",
      "enGB": "The Black Blade gains a +1 bonus on damage rolls. For every four levels beyond 1st, this bonus increases by 1.",
      "enGB": "Black Blade Strike",
      "enGB": "At 13th level a magus can attempt to siphon points from his black blade’s arcane pool into his own arcane pool. Doing so takes a full-round action and the magus must succeed at a Will saving throw with a DC equal to the black blade’s ego. If the magus succeeds, he regains 1 point to his arcane pool for every 2 points he saps from his black blade. If he fails the saving throw, the magus becomes fatigued. If he is fatigued, he becomes exhausted instead. He cannot use this ability if he is exhausted.",
      "enGB": "Transfer Arcana",
      "enGB": "Transfer Arcana — Magus",
      "enGB": "At 13th level an arcanist can attempt to siphon points from his black blade’s arcane pool into his own arcane reservoir. Doing so takes a full-round action and the arcanist must succeed at a Will saving throw with a DC equal to the black blade’s ego. If the arcanist succeeds, he regains 1 point to his arcane reservoir for every 2 points he saps from his black blade. If he fails the saving throw, the magus becomes fatigued. If he is fatigued, he becomes exhausted instead. He cannot use this ability if he is exhausted.",
      "enGB": "Transfer Arcana — Arcanist",
      "enGB": "1 round/mythic rank",
      "enGB": "Reflex negates/Fortitude partial",
      "enGB": "A small number of arcanists learn to use blades as part of their spellcasting and in combat. While these blade adepts are not as capable with a sword as a true master duelist, their combination of swordplay and arcane power makes them quite deadly.",
      "enGB": "Blade Adept",
      "enGB": "Instead of the normal arcane pool amount, the bladebound magus’s arcane pool has a number of points equal to 1/3 his level (minimum 1) plus his Intelligence bonus.",
      "enGB": "A select group of magi are called to carry a black blade, a sentient weapon of often unknown and possibly unknowable purpose. These weapons become valuable tools and allies, as both the magus and weapon typically crave arcane power, but as a black blade becomes more aware, its true motivations manifest, and as does its ability to influence its wielder with its ever-increasing ego.",
      "enGB": "Bladebound (TTT)",
      "enGB": "Bleed",
      "enGB": "Bleeding Attack",
      "enGB": "A rogue with this ability can cause living opponents to bleed by hitting them with a sneak attack. This attack causes the target to take 1 additional point of damage each round for each die of the rogue’s sneak attack (e.g., 4d6 equals 4 points of bleed). Bleeding creatures take that amount of damage every round at the start of each of their turns. The bleeding can be stopped by the application of any effect that heals hit point damage. Bleed damage from this ability does not stack with itself. Bleed damage bypasses any damage reduction the creature might possess.",
      "enGB": "Blessed Claws",
      "enGB": "Blessed Claws — Chaotic",
      "enGB": "Blessed Claws — Evil",
      "enGB": "This ability functions as the shifter’s claws class feature, except the holy beast shifter’s default claws are long and thin, dealing piercing damage. At 3rd level, her claws are treated as one type of aligned weapon (chaotic, evil, good, or lawful) within one step of her deity’s alignment in addition to ignoring DR/cold iron, DR/magic, and DR/silver.\nAt will, a shifter in her natural form can extend her claws as a <b><color=#703565><link=\"Encyclopedia:Swift_Action\">swift action</link></color></b> to use as a weapon. The claws on each hand can be used as a primary <b><color=#703565><link=\"Encyclopedia:NaturalAttack\">natural attack</link></color></b>, dealing <b><color=#703565><link=\"Encyclopedia:Dice\">1d4</link></color></b> points of <b><color=#703565><link=\"Encyclopedia:Damage_Type\">piercing and slashing damage</link></color></b> (1d3 if she is <b><color=#703565><link=\"Encyclopedia:Size\">Small</link></color></b>). As the shifter gains levels, the power of her claws increases. At 3rd level, her claws bypass <b><color=#703565><link=\"Encyclopedia:Damage_Reduction\">DR</link></color></b> N/cold iron, N/magic, and N/silver. At 7th level, her claw damage increases to 1d6 (1d4 if Small). At 11th level, her claw damage increases to 1d8 (1d6 if Small). At 13th level, her claw damage increases to 1d10 (1d8 if Small). At 17th level, the damage die does not increase, but the <b><color=#703565><link=\"Encyclopedia:Critical\">critical</link></color></b> multiplier becomes ×3. Finally, at 19th level, the claws bypass DR N/adamantine and N/—.\nWhile a shifter uses wild shape to assume her aspect's major form, her primary natural <b><color=#703565><link=\"Encyclopedia:Attack\">attacks</link></color></b> gain the same benefits granted by her shifter claws ability. She can use either the base damage of her shifter claws or the damage of the form's primary attacks, whichever is greater. A list of primary attacks is provided in the description of each major form.",
      "enGB": "Blessed Claws — Good",
      "enGB": "Blessed Claws — Lawful",
      "enGB": "At 3rd level, her claws are treated as one type of aligned weapon (chaotic, evil, good, or lawful) within one step of her deity’s alignment in addition to ignoring DR/cold iron, DR/magic, and DR/silver.",
      "enGB": "At 20th level, the sorcerer gains the final power of thier bloodline.",
      "enGB": "Bloodline Capstone",
      "enGB": "Whenever you cast a spell with the electricity descriptor, that spell deals +1 point of damage per die rolled.",
      "enGB": "Whenever you cast a spell with the acid descriptor, that spell deals +1 point of damage per die rolled.",
      "enGB": "Whenever you cast a spell with the fire descriptor, that spell deals +1 point of damage per die rolled.",
      "enGB": "Whenever you cast a spell with the cold descriptor, that spell deals +1 point of damage per die rolled.",
      "enGB": "Whenever you cast a spell that deals energy damage, you can change the type of damage to match the type of your bloodline. This also changes the spell’s type to match the type of your bloodline.",
      "enGB": "Bloodline Requisite Feature",
      "enGB": "Bloodline",
      "enGB": "Dragon Disciple Bloodline",
      "enGB": "At 4th level, your limbs elongate and your reach increases by 5 feet.",
      "enGB": "Abnormal Reach",
      "enGB": "Aberrant Bloodrage",
      "enGB": "There is a taint in your blood that is both alien and bizarre. When you bloodrage, this manifests in peculiar and terrifying ways.\nWhile bloodraging, you gain the abilities and immunities of some aberrations, but show signs of your tainted heritage.\n<b><color=#703565><link=\"Encyclopedia:Bonus\">Bonus</link></color></b> Feats: Combat Reflexes, Great Fortitude, Improved Disarm, Improved Dirty Trick, Improved Initiative, Improved Unarmed Strike, Iron Will.\nBonus Spells: Enlarge Person (7th), See Invisibility (10th), Displacement (13th), Spike Stones (16th).",
      "enGB": "Aberrant",
      "enGB": "Bonus Feats: Combat Reflexes, Great Fortitude, Improved Disarm, Improved Dirty Trick, Improved Initiative, Improved Unarmed Strike, Iron Will.",
      "enGB": "Bonus Feats",
      "enGB": "At 20th level, your body becomes truly unnatural. You are immune to critical hits and sneak attacks. In addition, you gain blindsight with a range of 60 feet and your bloodrager damage reduction increases by 1. You have these benefits constantly, even while not bloodraging.",
      "enGB": "Aberrant Form",
      "enGB": "At 8th level, you become immune to the sickened and nauseated conditions.",
      "enGB": "Aberrant Fortitude",
      "enGB": "At 16th level, you are immune to disease, exhaustion, fatigue, and poison, and to the staggered condition.",
      "enGB": "Aberrant Resistance",
      "enGB": "Bonus Spell — See Invisibility",
      "enGB": "Bonus Spell — Displacement",
      "enGB": "Bonus Spell — Spike Stones",
      "enGB": "Bonus Spell — Enlarge Person",
      "enGB": "At 1st level, when you confirm a critical hit the target must succeed at a Fortitude saving throw or be staggered for 1 round. The DC of this save is equal to 10 + 1/2 your bloodrager level + your Constitution modifier. These effects stack with the Staggering Critical feat; the target must save against each effect individually.",
      "enGB": "Staggering Strike",
      "enGB": "At 12th level, your internal anatomy shifts and changes, giving you a 50% chance to negate any critical hit or sneak attack that hits you. The damage is instead rolled normally.",
      "enGB": "Unusual Anatomy",
      "enGB": "At 4th level, when entering a bloodrage, you can choose to grow one size category larger than your base size (as enlarge person) even if you aren't humanoid.",
      "enGB": "Abyssal Bulk",
      "enGB": "Greater Arcane Bloodrage: Haste",
      "enGB": "Arcane Bloodrage: Blur",
      "enGB": "While Raging",
      "enGB": "Arcane Bloodrage: Protection From Arrows",
      "enGB": "Arcane Bloodrage: Resist Acid",
      "enGB": "Arcane Bloodrage: Resist Cold",
